      "Witness statements and documentation gathered"
    ],
    "summary": "On 21 April 2023 at 0938 hours, the Transocean Discoverer Inspiration drillship experienced an intense frontal passage with 67 knot winds during well abandonment operations. The drillship drifted off location due to unforeseen wind shift and reduced thruster capacity, triggering the Emergency Disconnect System. The EDS performed as intended, discharging 513 barrels of calcium bromide into Gulf of Mexico waters. No injuries or equipment damage occurred.",
